pythagoras.f

Interface XY

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IPoint, IVector
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPoint, AbstractVector, Point, Vector

    public interface XY
    Defines an x/y coordinate. This is implemented by both Point and Vector so that APIs which require an x/y coordinate, but don't really want to mak the distinction between a translation vector versus a point in 2D space, can simply accept both.
